{"id": "28468", "post": "<div class=\"post-28468 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-editorial tag-bsd tag-freebsd tag-netbsd tag-openbsd tag-operating-system\" id=\"post-28468\"><h2 class=\"storytitle\"><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/openbsd-7-0-released/\" rel=\"bookmark\">OpenBSD 7.0 Released</a></h2><div class=\"meta\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" data-src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" alt=\"Tags: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/bsd/\" rel=\"tag\">BSD</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/freebsd/\" rel=\"tag\">freebsd</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/netbsd/\" rel=\"tag\">netbsd</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/openbsd/\" rel=\"tag\">openbsd</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/operating-system/\" rel=\"tag\">operating system</a> <img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" alt=\"Date/Time: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> October 14, 2021 @ 5:35 pm, by raindog308</div><div class=\"storycontent tablelook\"><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/OpenBSD_StarryPointers-s.png\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-28469 litespeed-loaded\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/OpenBSD_StarryPointers-s.png\" alt=\"OpenBSD 7.0\" width=\"227\" height=\"303\" align=\"right\" hspace=\"20\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/OpenBSD_StarryPointers-s.png 227w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/OpenBSD_StarryPointers-s-225x300.png 225w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 227px) 100vw, 227px\" sizes=\"(max-width: 227px) 100vw, 227px\" srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/OpenBSD_StarryPointers-s.png 227w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/OpenBSD_StarryPointers-s-225x300.png 225w\" data-was-processed=\"true\">The OpenBSD project announced the <a href=\"https://www.openbsd.org/70.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">release of OpenBSD 7.0</a> today. This is the 51st release of the operating system.</p><p>Major new features in this release include:</p><ul><li>Support for a new riscv64 platform, which is used by some boards such as the SiFive HighFive and PolarFire Icicle.</li><li>Continued support for Apple Silicon, though not to a production-ready level yet.</li><li>Improved handling for kernel config and kernel tracing on some platforms.</li><li>Increased vmd (OpenBSD\u2019s virtualization hypervisor) features, including support for up to 512 allocated vcpus.</li><li>Support for new hardware periphrials.</li><li>Many bug fixes.</li></ul><p>See the <a href=\"https://www.openbsd.org/70.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">release notes</a> for full details.&nbsp; And don\u2019t forgot to download the <a href=\"https://www.openbsd.org/lyrics.html#70\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">release song</a> for this version!</p><div class=\"relpost-thumb-wrapper\"><div class=\"relpost-thumb-container\"><h3>Related posts:</h3><div style=\"clear: both\"></div><div style=\"clear: both\"></div><div class=\"relpost-block-container\"><a class=\"relpost-block-single\" href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/lowendboxtv-ranking-the-vps-operating-system-choices-into-tiers/\"><div class=\"relpost-custom-block-single\" style=\"width: 150px; height: 215px;\"><div class=\"relpost-block-single-image\" alt=\"LowEndBoxTV: Ranking the VPS Operating System Choices into Tiers!\" style=\"background: transparent url(https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/tiers-vps-os-leb-3-150x150.png.webp) no-repeat scroll 0% 0%; width: 150px; height: 150px;\"></div><div class=\"relpost-block-single-text\" style=\"font-family: Arial;  font-size: 12px;  color: #333333;\">LowEndBoxTV: Rankin